        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Island_City"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The 1980s rezoning of Queens Plaza spurred office construction while preservationists fought to protect landmarks like the Sohmer Piano Factory and the Pepsi‑Cola sign.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.cityneighborhoods.nyc/long-island-city"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Greater Astoria Historical Society, founded in 1985, documents Long Island City’s history.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Island_City"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The 755‑foot Sven tower, completed at Queens Plaza, became Long Island City’s third‑tallest building.",
